<TEXT>
a dissident faction within the 
governing christian democrats has formally split with the party 
further weakening the party as it faces a challenge from the right 
the group led by former cabinet minister julio adolfo rey 
prendes filed with the central elections council on monday to 
establish the authentic christian movement or mac it also 
incorporated a tiny rightist party 
the petition is expected to be approved in a matter of days 
we control 80 percent of the structure and organization of the 
christian democratic party nationwide rey prendes told 
journalists at the elections council 
rey prendes lost the christian democratic nomination for the 
march 1989 presidential election to fidel chavez mena also a 
former cabinet minister president jose napoleon duarte and old 
friend and mentor of rey prendes was unable to mend the rift 
the division weakens the christian democrats who have governed 
since 1984 but face an uphill battle in the election against the 
rightist republican nationalist alliance known by its spanish 
acronym arena 
arena won 32 seats in the 60seat legislature in elections last 
march it also won control of two thirds of el salvadors 
municipalities 
rey prendes said his group hoped to finish second in the first 
round of the presidential election which will probably be decided 
in a runoff 
arena is considered likely to get the biggest share of the vote 
but not a majority in the first round 
the christian democratic split produces a confusing situation in 
the legislature seventeen of the partys 22 legislators are loyal 
to rey prendes how the new faction will vote remains to be seen 
duarte who is suffering from terminal cancer told journalists 
saturday the split was a shame but now its a fact and we 
just have to press ahead 
</TEXT>
