<TEXT>
three previous national book awards winners 
don delillo jf powers and peter gay were among the 10 nominees 
announced for the 1988 awards 
delillo who won in 1985 for white noise was nominated for 
libra a novel based on the life of lee harvey oswald and the 
events that led to president john f kennedys assassination 
powers who won in 1963 for his novel morte durban is up 
for the fiction honor again with wheat that springeth green a 
novel about a middleaged priest coping with a new curate 
gay who won in 1967 for the enlightenment an 
interpretation was again nominated for nonfiction for his 
biography freud a life for our time 
the national book awards were established in 1950 winners will 
be announced in new york on nov 29 awards are given for fiction 
and nonfiction with each winner receiving a 10000 prize and a 
commemorative sculpture by louise nevelson 
other nominees for fiction 
pete dexter whose novel paris trout concerns the murder of 
a 14yearold black girl by a white man in a small georgia town 
just after world war ii 
mary mcgarry morris whose first novel vanished is about 
a couple who kidnap a toddler and embark on a fiveyear flight from 
justice 
anne tyler whose novel breathing lessons concerns a 
longmarried couple and the detours they take on the way to the 
funeral of an old friend in pennsylvania 
the other nominees for nonfiction 
reconstruction americas unfinished revolution 18631877 
by eric foner 
nora by brenda maddox a biography of james joyces 
lifelong companion and muse 
jefferson and monticello jack mclaughlins chronicle of 
the life of thomas jefferson as seen through the prism of his love 
for his rural homestead 
a bright shining lie john paul vann and america in 
vietnam by neil sheehan which examines the war through the eyes 
of one who lived most of his adult life in the midst of it 
</TEXT>
