here are some provisions of the catchall tax 
bill on which a final senate vote was expected tonight 
corrections the bill corrects hundreds of errors in the 1986 
tax overhaul 
diesel farms and other businesses that use diesel fuel for 
offroad purposes would be relieved from paying the federal tax and 
then applying for a refund 
bill of rights taxpayers would be given new protections in 
dealings with the internal revenue service the irs would be barred 
from using collections quotas to promote workers 
freelancers certain writers photographers and artists would 
be allowed to deduct expenses even before a project produces income 
higher education families could avoid tax on interest earned 
on us savings bonds that are redeemed to pay for colllege or 
vocational school 
telephone no deduction would be allowed for the basic monthly 
charge for a home telephone 
extensions several expiring provisions would be extended for 
brief periods including an exemption for bonds that help 
lowerincome families buy their first home a credit for increased 
business research and a benefit for workers who receive 
employerpaid legal or educational assistance 
heifer tax individual livestock farmers would be relieved 
from this tax which prohibits them from deducting costs of 
producing an animal until the animal produces income 
