rights suit is an extreme measure it is necessary when the 
prejudice to the defendant can be avoided in no other way 
the case began in april 1972 when the newspaper guild on behalf 
of its female members filed a charge with the federal equal 
employment opportunity commission 
the complaint accused the newspaper of sex discrimination in its 
handling of merit pay promotions and assignments and in other 
employment practices 
four years passed before the eeoc began its investigation 
another six years elapsed before the union and its members sued the 
plain dealer in federal court 
