with the commissions investigation does not explain the initial 
fouryear delay in launching the probe 
the appeals court noted that the trial judge who dismissed the 
suit initially had found that the eeocs notice to defendant to 
retain personnel records was too ambiguous to serve as a valid 
command 
the case is cleveland newspaper guild vs plain dealer 871864 
