<TEXT>
the senate putting the finishing touches on a 
27 billion tax bill that would dole out special benefits to 
selected individuals and businesses refused today to boost a 
special tax benefit for lowincome working families 
on an 852 vote the senate defeated an amendment by sen bill 
bradley dnj that would have raised the maximum earnedincome 
credit for families from 875 to 978 a year bradley would have 
financed the increase by deleting from the bill several provisions 
that would have helped corporations and some individuals 
