three evangelists who traveled the southern 
revival circuit pleaded guilty tuesday to running an interstate sex 
ring of boys they recruited with gifts and money and then molested 
mario tony leyva rias edward morris and freddie m herring 
entered guilty pleas to federal charges they used the tony leyva 
evangelistic association inc based in columbus ga to recruit 
boys for homosexual prostitution 
dozens of boys told investigators they were given money lodging 
and gifts in return for letting the preachers molest them the 
evangelists were not accused of selling the boys services to 
others 
